A. Functional Requirements
The system must allow customer registration of devices.

The system must capture customer details (name, phone number).

The system must record device details (sticker number, charger, bag).

The system must record device problem description.

The system must indicate whether repair is internal or external.

The system must track repair status.

The system must calculate repair cost and profit.

The system must record service type (pickup, drop-off, customer delivery).

The system must allow updating repair progress.

The system must store all records in a database (SQLite)

B. Non-Functional Requirements

Usability:

System shall be easy to use for non-technical staff

Interface shall allow device registration within 2 minutes

Deployability:

System shall run on Linux (Ubuntu)

System shall run using Rust backend

Maintainable:

Code shall be modular

Documentation shall be included in repository

Scalability:

System must support 100+ repair records

Security:

Customer data shall be stored securely

Only authorized users can access system

Performance:

System shall load records within 2 seconds
